# ============================================
# DEVELOPMENT NOTES
# ============================================
# 
# 1. Database Service:
#    - Uses SQLite for local data storage
#    - Automatically creates necessary tables
#    - Stores API cache, custom data, logs, and configuration
#
# 2. Cache Service:
#    - Tries Redis first (if available)
#    - Falls back to SQLite if Redis is unavailable
#    - Configurable TTL and key prefixes
#
# 3. Admin Interface:
#    - Available at /admin
#    - Provides web-based management interface
#    - Monitor system status, cache, database, and logs
#
# 4. Security:
#    - Rate limiting on API endpoints
#    - Helmet for HTTP security headers
#    - CORS enabled for cross-origin requests
#
# 5. Monitoring:
#    - Automatic logging of API calls
#    - System health checks
#    - Performance metrics and statistics
